                            <comment id="65375" author="linda" created="Thu, 29 Aug 2013 16:10:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since this ticket is being addressed by Avadhani J, it will not be addressed as part of the Lustre Manual Improvement project.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="54497" author="jonna09" created="Wed, 20 Mar 2013 18:57:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is where I am right now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My idea was to explain LNET routing in more detail. Once I picked this task up, I felt that LNET itself needed more explanation. So currently, I am working on improving Chapter 2 and making a good deal of addition to chapter 9. Most of that is done. I will try to submit these changes, hopefully by next week.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now as far as, LNET/LND credits and flow control is concerned, we have seen the effects of tweaking LNET kernel module paramters, however, we unfortunately haven&apos;t been able to simulate or create a complex enough test bench to actually see the results of tweaking respective LND kernel module parameters . Hence, I do not have complete clarity to write on this subject.....yet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have also noticed the recent addition of a new chapter on this topic. I will add what I can to this new chapter. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you would like to assign the ticket, please do so. I will try and contribute as much as I can.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="54399" author="rhenwood" created="Tue, 19 Mar 2013 17:28:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Avadhani,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to Assign this ticket to you. Have you hit any issues while compiling your contribution to the Manual?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers,&lt;br/&gt;
Richard&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53045" author="jonna09" created="Tue, 26 Feb 2013 13:55:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I know this discussion, I was involved in it as well. @Richard: Thanks for the heads up, I will make it a point to include this as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49967" author="rhenwood" created="Fri, 4 Jan 2013 14:14:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree. I saw your posting and it would be excellent to put this into a section in the Manual and I think you&apos;re the best person for this!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
